NOTES from during converstion to a machine readable datafile

McMaster, both departments, provide “more to offset higher tuition” to the international MSc students, but the amount is unspecified.

Summary information

There were 140 programs within the final dataset, from 38 Universities. There are 71 MSc and 69 PhD programs. Of all of these different degree programs, 50.7142857% were classified as closest to Ecology, while 49.2857143% are in Physics.

Mean domestic tuition was 5824.5583214CAD, median 6240.165CAD. Mean international tuition was 1.5312914^{4}CAD, median 1.497777^{4}CAD. Mean domestic fees were 1681.3175758CAD, international mean 2279.1507576CAD. Total tuition and fees domestic mean is 7376.2457321CAD, while international total was 1.7434514^{4}CAD.

Of the 140 programs within the final dataset, 98 programs have a minimum, while 21 had no information provided that we could access and did not respond to our requests. The average domestic minimum stipend provided was 2.3878032^{4}CAD, median 2.415^{4}CAD. When support is different than domestic support, international minimum gross stipend mean is 3.0219923^{4}CAD. Net domestic mean is 1.6407019^{4}CAD while median 1.729052^{4}CAD.

Mean tuition Get score: 0.6942149 Mean tuition Parse score: 1.214876 Mean Stipend Get score: 1.5982906 Mean Stipend Complete score: 0.8103448

Students repay 32.7158959% back to the university in the form of tuition and fees.

Mean MBM Shortfall Domestic: -9681.9087147 Mean MBM Shortfall International: -1.6779702^{4}

difference between US and Canada: NA
